  "prompt": "Has a movie ever been shot in space?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, a feature film has not been fully shot in space in the way that films are typically produced on Earth. However, there have been notable projects that involve space:\n\n1. **\"The Infinite\" (2021)**: This is a short film that was filmed partially in space. It features footage shot on the International Space Station (ISS).\n\n2. **\"Space Station 3D\" (2002)**: This is a documentary filmed on the ISS, showcasing life and scientific research on the space station.\n\n3. **\"Axiom Space's film project\"**: In March 2021, Axiom Space announced plans to create a feature film onboard the ISS, which would mark one of the first narrative films shot in space.\n\nWhile these projects involve shooting in or around space, a full-length narrative film set entirely in space that adhered to traditional filming practices was yet to occur. Keep an eye out for further developments in this exciting area!",
